radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 1.5 cm and is fluid-filled, with a calcified appendicolith at the tip. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, gastrointestinal tract, urinary bladder, and reproductive organs are unremarkable. No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy. No evidence of abdominal aortic aneurysm or acute fracture.
